# Keep the Vercel deployment lean: upload only what `next build` (and the
# postbuild sitemap step) actually needs. Everything below is local tooling,
# agent state, docs, or separate services that must NOT be part of the Vercel
# build/deploy — shipping them bloats provisioning and, for the container
# services, triggers Functions auto-detection that times out on the free plan.
#
# Patterns are root-anchored (leading slash) so they only match top-level
# entries and never app code (e.g. src/lib/directus/ stays included).

# Standalone container services (run on Fly/Render/local or opt-in paid Vercel).
/backend/
/directus/

# Agent control plane, skills, and generated knowledge graphs.
/.agents/
/.claude/
/.learnings/
/graphify-out/

# Local git hooks and CI config (not needed at build time).
/.husky/
/.github/

# Non-app sources and fixtures.
/remotion/
/supabase/
/tests/

# Operating manuals / docs (kept in the repo, not shipped to Vercel).
/agents.md
/CLAUDE.md
